I would like to be given the option to group the shared links by topic on the Shared Links Index page.
Preferably, the topics would be headings to separate the lists of links rather than just a single list sorted by topic.
For example, if I look at the Templates tab in Space Tools, the templates for Product Requirements page and index are grouped under a heading of Product Requirements.

h3. Workaround

*Note:* This workaround requires you to edit the "Custom HTML" settings in Confluence, which we classify as a "customization" to Confluence. Please keep track of this change and ensure that if/when you upgrade Confluence to a newer version, you verify whether or not this customization should remain in place or be removed.

# Go to the "Custom HTML" section of the Confluence Administration Console.
# Add the following text to the "At end of the HEAD" section:
{code:javascript}
<script type="text/javascript">
var $ = jQuery;
</script>
{code}

It should look like this:

!^customhtml.png!

*Note:* If you already have some other content in this section, you will need to merge it together with this addition.

