It would be useful to have an option to simply disable the ability to see the Page History of pages on a specific space.

The idea of this improvement would to maintain Confluence saving the page history information but making not possible for users to delete the previous versions (either by accident or with malicious intent).

When implementing a Custom Theme the footer of the website breaks because the sidebar.css style is only applied to the Default Theme.

If we take a look at the CSS selector for the footer on the Default Theme we will find: 
{code:none}
.theme-default .ia-splitter #footer {
  /* The content is not relevant.*/
  width: auto;
  position: absolute;
  right: 0;
  left: 0;
}
{code}

So, whenever we create our own theme the *body* element will not take the class *theme-default* and the style will never be applied, breaking the layout. 

Attached you may find the screenshots that prove this.

