The page [Database JDBC Drivers|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONF52/Database+JDBC+Drivers] needs to be updated.

Where it says:
{quote}* For Oracle 11.1, use the 10.2.0.4 or 11.1.0.7.0 driver (Java 6 ojdbc6.jar).
* For Oracle 11.2, use the 11.2.0.1.0 driver (Java 6 ojdbc6.jar).{quote}

It mentions Java 6 which is not Compatible with Confluence since 5.0. It should reference Java 7 instead.

Newer version of the drivers are also backwards compatible. I think we should recommend to use the latest possible version of the JDBC driver instead. We should make sure it gets on well with Confluence before recommending it.

